00:00:20.090 --> 00:00:22.940 align:middle line:10%
What mysteries
are to be revealed

00:00:22.940 --> 00:00:27.500 align:middle line:10%
within the deepest parts of
our brain and body system?

00:00:27.500 --> 00:00:31.190 align:middle line:10%
An exciting new frontier in
both science and medicine

00:00:31.190 --> 00:00:34.970 align:middle line:10%
is investigating how both
the gut and the heart

00:00:34.970 --> 00:00:38.840 align:middle line:10%
operate as two
independent brain centers.

00:00:38.840 --> 00:00:41.910 align:middle line:84%
Not only that, but
the more we learn,

00:00:41.910 --> 00:00:43.730 align:middle line:84%
the more we realize
that the brain

00:00:43.730 --> 00:00:46.070 align:middle line:84%
in the gut and the
brain in the heart

00:00:46.070 --> 00:00:50.190 align:middle line:84%
are more primary than
the brain in the head.

00:00:50.190 --> 00:00:54.440 align:middle line:10%
Our concept of the brain is thus
expanding into a more holistic

00:00:54.440 --> 00:00:56.780 align:middle line:10%
framework as
science is beginning

00:00:56.780 --> 00:01:01.570 align:middle line:10%
to recognize that there are
three brains in our body.

00:01:01.570 --> 00:01:03.850 align:middle line:84%
How does this brain
within the gut

00:01:03.850 --> 00:01:08.050 align:middle line:84%
fit in with our exploration
of consciousness?

00:01:08.050 --> 00:01:11.710 align:middle line:84%
To answer that, let's
begin by taking a look

00:01:11.710 --> 00:01:14.830 align:middle line:90%
at the intelligence of the gut.

00:01:14.830 --> 00:01:18.610 align:middle line:84%
The gut has its own
independent brain system known

00:01:18.610 --> 00:01:21.650 align:middle line:90%
as the enteric nervous system.

00:01:21.650 --> 00:01:25.660 align:middle line:84%
This system is composed
of 100 million nerve cells

00:01:25.660 --> 00:01:28.760 align:middle line:84%
lining the
gastrointestinal tract.

00:01:28.760 --> 00:01:31.870 align:middle line:84%
That's more nerve cells
than the spinal column

00:01:31.870 --> 00:01:34.180 align:middle line:90%
and peripheral nervous system.

00:01:34.180 --> 00:01:37.470 align:middle line:84%
Talk about a
mind-blowing discovery.

00:01:37.470 --> 00:01:40.630 align:middle line:84%
This system is
responsible for managing

00:01:40.630 --> 00:01:43.780 align:middle line:84%
our digestive processes,
and it sends signals

00:01:43.780 --> 00:01:48.580 align:middle line:84%
to the brain to alert us when
there's any sort of imbalance.

00:01:48.580 --> 00:01:51.670 align:middle line:84%
Scientists are finding this
communication is directly

00:01:51.670 --> 00:01:54.490 align:middle line:84%
connected to the limbic
system and discoveries

00:01:54.490 --> 00:01:56.770 align:middle line:84%
are leading to new
breakthroughs in how

00:01:56.770 --> 00:02:00.387 align:middle line:84%
we think of the gut and
the brain relationship.

00:02:00.387 --> 00:02:03.250 align:middle line:90%


00:02:03.250 --> 00:02:05.140 align:middle line:84%
When we feel
anxious or stressed,

00:02:05.140 --> 00:02:08.990 align:middle line:84%
we have abdominal pain or
butterflies in the stomach.

00:02:08.990 --> 00:02:11.110 align:middle line:84%
Or if the digestive
system isn't doing well,

00:02:11.110 --> 00:02:14.350 align:middle line:90%
we can feel moody or depressed.

00:02:14.350 --> 00:02:18.400 align:middle line:84%
It was once thought that anxiety
and depression caused issues

00:02:18.400 --> 00:02:20.450 align:middle line:90%
within the digestive system.

00:02:20.450 --> 00:02:25.150 align:middle line:84%
But now, research is finding
it's more often the other way

00:02:25.150 --> 00:02:27.180 align:middle line:90%
around.

00:02:27.180 --> 00:02:30.000 align:middle line:84%
How is this
communication happening?

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:33.210 align:middle line:84%
Well, this brings us
back to the vagus nerve.

00:02:33.210 --> 00:02:36.090 align:middle line:84%
Not only does the vagus
nerve play a critical role

00:02:36.090 --> 00:02:39.000 align:middle line:84%
in communication between
the heart and the brain,

00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:42.870 align:middle line:84%
but it's also a key player
in the brain and the gut's

00:02:42.870 --> 00:02:44.880 align:middle line:90%
connection.

00:02:44.880 --> 00:02:49.110 align:middle line:84%
And this nerve runs from
the top of the spinal cord

00:02:49.110 --> 00:02:52.020 align:middle line:90%
to all major organs in our body.

00:02:52.020 --> 00:02:55.320 align:middle line:84%
It's the main component of our
parasympathetic nervous system

00:02:55.320 --> 00:02:58.740 align:middle line:84%
that controls our
ability to relax.

00:02:58.740 --> 00:03:02.280 align:middle line:84%
Stimulating the vagus
nerve fibers within the gut

00:03:02.280 --> 00:03:06.390 align:middle line:84%
influences the brain stem
and the limbic system.

00:03:06.390 --> 00:03:10.800 align:middle line:84%
Fascinating new research
shows that toning these fibers

00:03:10.800 --> 00:03:13.920 align:middle line:84%
reduces mood and
anxiety disorders,

00:03:13.920 --> 00:03:16.890 align:middle line:90%
like depression and PTSD.

00:03:16.890 --> 00:03:19.240 align:middle line:90%
So how do we do it?

00:03:19.240 --> 00:03:22.670 align:middle line:90%
How do we tone these fibers?

00:03:22.670 --> 00:03:28.260 align:middle line:84%
One simple method is using deep
and slow breathing techniques,

00:03:28.260 --> 00:03:32.040 align:middle line:84%
like we use in meditation,
especially when we

00:03:32.040 --> 00:03:35.250 align:middle line:84%
slow our breathing rate
down to a rate of five

00:03:35.250 --> 00:03:38.500 align:middle line:90%
to seven breaths per minute.

00:03:38.500 --> 00:03:42.180 align:middle line:84%
We can achieve this by
breathing in to a count of five,

00:03:42.180 --> 00:03:44.280 align:middle line:84%
hold the breath for
a count of five,

00:03:44.280 --> 00:03:47.680 align:middle line:84%
and then exhale
to a count of 10.

00:03:47.680 --> 00:03:51.640 align:middle line:84%
So what is the gut
communicating to the brain?

00:03:51.640 --> 00:03:54.190 align:middle line:84%
Well, for one thing, it's
clear that it's about

00:03:54.190 --> 00:03:57.160 align:middle line:90%
a lot more than digestion.

00:03:57.160 --> 00:04:01.780 align:middle line:84%
The state of our gut impacts
our motivation, our higher

00:04:01.780 --> 00:04:06.010 align:middle line:84%
cognitive functions, memory,
intuitive decision-making,

00:04:06.010 --> 00:04:07.340 align:middle line:90%
and more.

00:04:07.340 --> 00:04:11.200 align:middle line:84%
There's a reason we talk
about having a gut feeling.

00:04:11.200 --> 00:04:14.890 align:middle line:84%
This information traveling
from the gut up to the brain

00:04:14.890 --> 00:04:18.200 align:middle line:84%
influences our
thoughts and emotions.

00:04:18.200 --> 00:04:19.990 align:middle line:84%
So science in the
West is just starting

00:04:19.990 --> 00:04:21.730 align:middle line:84%
to recognize how
the state of the gut

00:04:21.730 --> 00:04:24.130 align:middle line:90%
affects our overall well-being.

00:04:24.130 --> 00:04:26.650 align:middle line:84%
But for many ancient
wisdom traditions,

00:04:26.650 --> 00:04:29.080 align:middle line:90%
this isn't new information.

00:04:29.080 --> 00:04:32.440 align:middle line:84%
In traditional Chinese
medicine, each organ

00:04:32.440 --> 00:04:35.110 align:middle line:90%
is associated with an emotion.

00:04:35.110 --> 00:04:38.680 align:middle line:84%
Stimulating the meridian
system strengthens that organ

00:04:38.680 --> 00:04:41.410 align:middle line:90%
and restores balance.

00:04:41.410 --> 00:04:43.780 align:middle line:84%
The lungs and the
large intestine

00:04:43.780 --> 00:04:47.270 align:middle line:84%
correspond with things
like grief and depression.

00:04:47.270 --> 00:04:51.430 align:middle line:84%
While the heart and the small
intestine correspond with joy.

00:04:51.430 --> 00:04:54.370 align:middle line:84%
If we have an imbalance
in one of these organs,

00:04:54.370 --> 00:04:58.060 align:middle line:84%
we may be lacking in joy,
for example, or holding

00:04:58.060 --> 00:05:00.130 align:middle line:90%
onto grief or sadness.

00:05:00.130 --> 00:05:03.430 align:middle line:84%
And our emotions, they
can be stored in our body

00:05:03.430 --> 00:05:06.400 align:middle line:84%
and affect the
function of our organs.

00:05:06.400 --> 00:05:09.550 align:middle line:84%
If the gut isn't working
properly, there will be issues.

00:05:09.550 --> 00:05:11.890 align:middle line:10%
And this can affect
our emotions, memory,

00:05:11.890 --> 00:05:16.780 align:middle line:10%
overall cognitive functions,
and our health as a whole.

00:05:16.780 --> 00:05:20.230 align:middle line:84%
For a long time, we
thought of the brain

00:05:20.230 --> 00:05:23.110 align:middle line:84%
as the mainframe that
sends the signals

00:05:23.110 --> 00:05:25.030 align:middle line:90%
to the rest of the body.

00:05:25.030 --> 00:05:27.160 align:middle line:84%
But now, we're seeing
that the deeper

00:05:27.160 --> 00:05:30.550 align:middle line:84%
roots of this system,
the gut and the heart,

00:05:30.550 --> 00:05:34.870 align:middle line:84%
are driving our brain
and daily consciousness.

00:05:34.870 --> 00:05:37.420 align:middle line:84%
Through this season
of Mystery Teachings,

00:05:37.420 --> 00:05:41.140 align:middle line:84%
we've been exploring how to
waken our greater potential

00:05:41.140 --> 00:05:44.590 align:middle line:84%
and access transcendent
states of consciousness.

00:05:44.590 --> 00:05:48.610 align:middle line:84%
To do so, we must build
bridges deeper and deeper

00:05:48.610 --> 00:05:52.390 align:middle line:84%
into our brain-body system
so that we can intentionally

00:05:52.390 --> 00:05:54.220 align:middle line:90%
influence it.

00:05:54.220 --> 00:05:56.770 align:middle line:84%
Our next step on this
journey is to create

00:05:56.770 --> 00:06:00.190 align:middle line:84%
a state of homeostasis
within the gut

00:06:00.190 --> 00:06:05.140 align:middle line:84%
and harness the full power
of this third brain center.

00:06:05.140 --> 00:06:09.820 align:middle line:84%
So what happens when the gut is
functioning at optimal levels?

00:06:09.820 --> 00:06:12.970 align:middle line:84%
Well, to answer this, let's
look at the bigger picture.

00:06:12.970 --> 00:06:17.590 align:middle line:84%
In many ancient traditions,
the more holistic perspective

00:06:17.590 --> 00:06:20.860 align:middle line:84%
is that it's one of
three primary energy

00:06:20.860 --> 00:06:23.150 align:middle line:90%
centers within the body.

00:06:23.150 --> 00:06:26.530 align:middle line:84%
Within Eastern qigong
and Daoist traditions,

00:06:26.530 --> 00:06:29.860 align:middle line:84%
these areas are known as
the upper, the middle,

00:06:29.860 --> 00:06:33.306 align:middle line:84%
and the lower
tanden, or dantian.

00:06:33.306 --> 00:06:36.620 align:middle line:84%
Now these are located at
the third eye, the heart,

00:06:36.620 --> 00:06:39.860 align:middle line:84%
and the hara, just
below the navel.

00:06:39.860 --> 00:06:42.620 align:middle line:84%
Is it any wonder that
these three locations

00:06:42.620 --> 00:06:47.090 align:middle line:84%
correspond with the brain,
the heart, and the guts?

00:06:47.090 --> 00:06:49.670 align:middle line:10%
These three energy
centers function

00:06:49.670 --> 00:06:54.560 align:middle line:10%
as storage areas for our
life force known as qi.

00:06:54.560 --> 00:06:56.910 align:middle line:84%
But each system
works differently

00:06:56.910 --> 00:07:00.210 align:middle line:84%
and with a different
quality of qi.

00:07:00.210 --> 00:07:03.020 align:middle line:84%
Now according to the Western
mystery school traditions,

00:07:03.020 --> 00:07:05.090 align:middle line:84%
these three energy
centers relate

00:07:05.090 --> 00:07:08.180 align:middle line:90%
to different levels of will.

00:07:08.180 --> 00:07:11.270 align:middle line:84%
The upper tanden,
or third eye, is

00:07:11.270 --> 00:07:15.290 align:middle line:84%
said to be our connection
to the will of our spirit.

00:07:15.290 --> 00:07:18.050 align:middle line:84%
It's our connection
to our eternal being--

00:07:18.050 --> 00:07:23.150 align:middle line:84%
the love, will, and vision
of our individuated spirit,

00:07:23.150 --> 00:07:25.930 align:middle line:90%
our original self.

00:07:25.930 --> 00:07:28.730 align:middle line:84%
The middle tanden,
or heart center,

00:07:28.730 --> 00:07:32.600 align:middle line:84%
is our connection to
the will of our soul.

00:07:32.600 --> 00:07:36.110 align:middle line:84%
It's our connection to the
love of our higher self,

00:07:36.110 --> 00:07:39.170 align:middle line:90%
and it's more personal to us.

00:07:39.170 --> 00:07:42.860 align:middle line:84%
There's a difference between
the soul and the spirit.

00:07:42.860 --> 00:07:45.470 align:middle line:84%
Now we can think of the
spirit as that big picture

00:07:45.470 --> 00:07:50.270 align:middle line:84%
perspective of who we are as
an infinite eternal being.

00:07:50.270 --> 00:07:53.660 align:middle line:10%
While our soul is more
personal and directly connected

00:07:53.660 --> 00:07:58.290 align:middle line:10%
to our purpose and our
contracts in this life.

00:07:58.290 --> 00:08:02.040 align:middle line:84%
The lower tanden, or
hara, located at the gut

00:08:02.040 --> 00:08:05.460 align:middle line:84%
is more of our
personal body's will.

00:08:05.460 --> 00:08:09.900 align:middle line:84%
This is our desires coming up
from the subconscious mind.

00:08:09.900 --> 00:08:15.150 align:middle line:84%
It includes the body's urges for
food, sex, life force, power,

00:08:15.150 --> 00:08:16.800 align:middle line:90%
and pleasure.

00:08:16.800 --> 00:08:22.380 align:middle line:84%
And it's our primary storage
energy center for our vitality.

00:08:22.380 --> 00:08:25.620 align:middle line:84%
So how does this relate
to consciousness?

00:08:25.620 --> 00:08:27.540 align:middle line:84%
To get a sense of
that, let's use

00:08:27.540 --> 00:08:31.470 align:middle line:84%
an analogy of a tree as
our neurological system.

00:08:31.470 --> 00:08:35.820 align:middle line:84%
The cortex is like the
upper leaves and branches.

00:08:35.820 --> 00:08:38.730 align:middle line:84%
The limbic system is
the lower branches.

00:08:38.730 --> 00:08:42.539 align:middle line:84%
While the brain stem is
like the trunk of the tree.

00:08:42.539 --> 00:08:46.500 align:middle line:10%
As we then go deeper from the
brainstem down to the heart

00:08:46.500 --> 00:08:51.510 align:middle line:10%
and, finally, to the gut, we're
coming into the deepest roots.

00:08:51.510 --> 00:08:55.830 align:middle line:84%
At the hara, we are at
the ends of the roots.

00:08:55.830 --> 00:08:58.260 align:middle line:84%
And this is where we
draw nourishment up

00:08:58.260 --> 00:09:02.840 align:middle line:84%
from the earth into our system
up through the root chakra.

00:09:02.840 --> 00:09:06.120 align:middle line:84%
The hara is then the
storage point, or reservoir,

00:09:06.120 --> 00:09:07.290 align:middle line:90%
of our body.

00:09:07.290 --> 00:09:10.110 align:middle line:84%
While the root chakra's how
we send that energy out to

00:09:10.110 --> 00:09:14.580 align:middle line:84%
manifest as well as draw
it up from the Earth.

00:09:14.580 --> 00:09:17.520 align:middle line:84%
As we go deeper
into this system,

00:09:17.520 --> 00:09:19.740 align:middle line:90%
our consciousness deepens.

00:09:19.740 --> 00:09:24.870 align:middle line:84%
The deeper we go, the more we
lose our sense of personality,

00:09:24.870 --> 00:09:30.960 align:middle line:84%
our masks dissolve, and we start
tapping into our core self.

00:09:30.960 --> 00:09:33.750 align:middle line:84%
Then as we go even
deeper, we begin

00:09:33.750 --> 00:09:37.860 align:middle line:84%
to finally dissolve that sense
of self as an individuated

00:09:37.860 --> 00:09:39.480 align:middle line:90%
being.

00:09:39.480 --> 00:09:41.940 align:middle line:84%
We begin to merge
with the collective

00:09:41.940 --> 00:09:44.280 align:middle line:84%
and, from the
collective, we go deeper

00:09:44.280 --> 00:09:47.250 align:middle line:90%
and merge with the oneness.

00:09:47.250 --> 00:09:50.220 align:middle line:90%
This is the final bridge--

00:09:50.220 --> 00:09:55.470 align:middle line:84%
the expansion of consciousness
into oneness with all things.

00:09:55.470 --> 00:09:57.870 align:middle line:84%
We're moving beyond
our individuated self

00:09:57.870 --> 00:10:01.300 align:middle line:90%
and into unity consciousness.

00:10:01.300 --> 00:10:06.310 align:middle line:84%
So how do we come into
this oneness experience?

00:10:06.310 --> 00:10:09.880 align:middle line:84%
To really experience that
oneness with the all,

00:10:09.880 --> 00:10:13.690 align:middle line:84%
we first have to go
through the void.

00:10:13.690 --> 00:10:16.210 align:middle line:84%
The void is what
mystics describe

00:10:16.210 --> 00:10:19.750 align:middle line:84%
as a state of
emptiness, nothingness,

00:10:19.750 --> 00:10:24.940 align:middle line:84%
no thing manifested yet
all potential exists.

00:10:24.940 --> 00:10:28.210 align:middle line:84%
From the perspective
of quantum physics,

00:10:28.210 --> 00:10:31.840 align:middle line:84%
we can relate the void
to the zero-point field.

00:10:31.840 --> 00:10:34.210 align:middle line:84%
This quantum view
can help us better

00:10:34.210 --> 00:10:37.000 align:middle line:84%
understand how to
connect with the void

00:10:37.000 --> 00:10:39.790 align:middle line:90%
to reach the state of oneness.

00:10:39.790 --> 00:10:42.550 align:middle line:84%
But first, we must
find the gateway,

00:10:42.550 --> 00:10:46.900 align:middle line:84%
or what is known in the quantum
physics realm as the gap.

00:10:46.900 --> 00:10:49.510 align:middle line:84%
We explored the gap
extensively in Season 1

00:10:49.510 --> 00:10:51.910 align:middle line:90%
of Mystery Teachings.

00:10:51.910 --> 00:10:54.910 align:middle line:84%
Shifting into quantum
awareness becomes possible

00:10:54.910 --> 00:10:57.220 align:middle line:90%
when we focus on the gap.

